"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tsn1665702922370.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsn1665702922370.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsn1665702922370.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tsn1665702922370\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Scalability\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__scalability_140060\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For coping with the more complex business applications of today and the growing number of concurrent users, adding more resources to the physical infrastructure, such as processing speed, memory, or disk space, is often done with the intention of increasing performance. However, adding hardware is not always sufficient and might not necessarily result in better performance. To efficiently use additional hardware, applications need to be scalable, that is, capable of executing pieces of the application logic on hardware specifically configured for the logic.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__p_d45521e1_d45522e1_d45523e1\">Client/server and Web applications can typically be deployed over multiple clients and servers, ranging from a single-tier to a multi-tier architecture. The multi-tier architecture allows an application to be executed over multiple part of the infrastructure.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__p_d45524e1_d45525e1_d45526e1\">Multi-tier architectures are typically split into the following parts:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22742e1_d22743e1_d22744e1\">Presentation tier—Components responsible for the user interface\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22745e1_d22746e1_d22747e1\">Business logic tier—Components for business rules and task-specific behavior\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22748e1_d22749e1_d22750e1\">Data access tier—Physical data access using SQL or other DML\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__p_d45527e1_d45528e1_d45529e1\">The advantages of multi-tier software architecture include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22751e1_d22752e1_d22753e1\">Scalability—The deployment infrastructure is easier to partition across available hardware\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22754e1_d22755e1_d22756e1\">Deployment flexibility—Specialized component roles\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22757e1_d22758e1_d22759e1\">Enhanced infrastructure independence—The three tiers are separated\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22760e1_d22761e1_d22762e1\">Clearly defined component roles—Both the development and the reuse of components is easier\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22763e1_d22764e1_d22765e1\">Stateless communication—Between the presentation and business logic tiers using XML\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tsn1665702922370__li_d22766e1_d22767e1_d22768e1\">Component-based development—Offering the ability to segregate skill sets\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532504\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532504\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Scalability Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Scalability For coping with the more complex business applications of today and the growing number of concurrent users, adding more resources to the physical infrastructure, such as processing speed, memory, or disk space, is often done with the intention of increasing performance. However, adding hardware is not always sufficient and might not necessarily result in better performance. To efficiently use additional hardware, applications need to be scalable, that is, capable of executing pieces of the application logic on hardware specifically configured for the logic. Client/server and Web applications can typically be deployed over multiple clients and servers, ranging from a single-tier to a multi-tier architecture. The multi-tier architecture allows an application to be executed over multiple part of the infrastructure. Multi-tier architectures are typically split into the following parts: Presentation tier—Components responsible for the user interface Business logic tier—Components for business rules and task-specific behavior Data access tier—Physical data access using SQL or other DML The advantages of multi-tier software architecture include: Scalability—The deployment infrastructure is easier to partition across available hardware Deployment flexibility—Specialized component roles Enhanced infrastructure independence—The three tiers are separated Clearly defined component roles—Both the development and the reuse of components is easier Stateless communication—Between the presentation and business logic tiers using XML Component-based development—Offering the ability to segregate skill sets Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}